newsitem.title: ARGENTINA: Argentine August industrial output up over 8.0 pct.
newsitem.headline: Argentine August industrial output up over 8.0 pct.

text.p: Argentina's industrial output climbed by more than 8.0 percent in August over August 1995, according to preliminary figures from the FIEL economic research institute Monday.
"With just two or three numbers still missing the index on a preliminary basis shows an increase of slightly more than eight percent," a source at FIEL told Reuters.
For the first time in 1996, accumulated industrial output when compared against the similar 1995 period showed an increase, he added.
FIEL is scheduled to release its preliminary production figures later Monday.
